<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="145" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1858,2027]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1930,1955]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Description.</emphasis>
General color yellowish. Head yellowish with M-line not distinct, parts of clypeal area yellowish and frons light brown (
<figureCitation box="[408,498,1966,1991]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1760,1783]" captionTargetBox="[339,1248,415,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[323,1268,405,1738]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – 2 D. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Male, 2 A, head and pronotum; 2 B – 2 D, penial armature (2 B dorsal, 2 C ventral and 2 D lateral views). Scales: Fig. 2 A 1.0 mm; Figs. 2 B – 2 D 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801871/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); lappets brown; clypeal area setose; post frontal line not distinct; scape and pedicel light brown; flagellomeres light brown; palpi light brown. Pronotum light brown with lighter rugosities (
<figureCitation box="[1332,1424,2002,2027]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1760,1783]" captionTargetBox="[339,1248,415,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[323,1268,405,1738]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – 2 D. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Male, 2 A, head and pronotum; 2 B – 2 D, penial armature (2 B dorsal, 2 C ventral and 2 D lateral views). Scales: Fig. 2 A 1.0 mm; Figs. 2 B – 2 D 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801871/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Legs yellowish to light brown, tibia and tarsi darker. Wing membrane light brown with veins darker. Cerci light brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">
Male: Forewing length 
<quantity box="[466,536,224,248]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" unit="mm" value="11.0">11mm</quantity>
(n=1). Penial armature (
<figureCitation box="[815,894,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1760,1783]" captionTargetBox="[339,1248,415,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[323,1268,405,1738]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – 2 D. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Male, 2 A, head and pronotum; 2 B – 2 D, penial armature (2 B dorsal, 2 C ventral and 2 D lateral views). Scales: Fig. 2 A 1.0 mm; Figs. 2 B – 2 D 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801871/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
B–2D), in ventral view, gradually tapering from medially to apex and terminating in an indistinct small aperture (
<figureCitation box="[884,952,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1760,1783]" captionTargetBox="[339,1248,415,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[323,1268,405,1738]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – 2 D. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Male, 2 A, head and pronotum; 2 B – 2 D, penial armature (2 B dorsal, 2 C ventral and 2 D lateral views). Scales: Fig. 2 A 1.0 mm; Figs. 2 B – 2 D 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801871/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
C), with a pair of small distal membranous vesicles (
<figureCitation box="[257,336,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1760,1783]" captionTargetBox="[339,1248,415,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[323,1268,405,1738]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – 2 D. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Male, 2 A, head and pronotum; 2 B – 2 D, penial armature (2 B dorsal, 2 C ventral and 2 D lateral views). Scales: Fig. 2 A 1.0 mm; Figs. 2 B – 2 D 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801871/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
C–2D); in lateral view, pronounced keel apparent (
<figureCitation box="[917,986,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1760,1783]" captionTargetBox="[339,1248,415,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[323,1268,405,1738]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – 2 D. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Male, 2 A, head and pronotum; 2 B – 2 D, penial armature (2 B dorsal, 2 C ventral and 2 D lateral views). Scales: Fig. 2 A 1.0 mm; Figs. 2 B – 2 D 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801871/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D), distinct in dorsal view appearing as two parallels bars (
<figureCitation box="[364,432,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1760,1783]" captionTargetBox="[339,1248,415,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[323,1268,405,1738]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – 2 D. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Male, 2 A, head and pronotum; 2 B – 2 D, penial armature (2 B dorsal, 2 C ventral and 2 D lateral views). Scales: Fig. 2 A 1.0 mm; Figs. 2 B – 2 D 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801871/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
B); hooks relatively short and flattened, little curved and with acute apices (
<figureCitation box="[1279,1346,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1760,1783]" captionTargetBox="[339,1248,415,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[323,1268,405,1738]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – 2 D. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Male, 2 A, head and pronotum; 2 B – 2 D, penial armature (2 B dorsal, 2 C ventral and 2 D lateral views). Scales: Fig. 2 A 1.0 mm; Figs. 2 B – 2 D 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801871/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801871/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" targetBox="[339,1248,415,1720]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1760,1813]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,352,1760,1783]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">FIGURES 2A–2D.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[360,548,1761,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pitii" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[360,548,1761,1783]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Anacroneuria pitii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[556,614,1761,1782]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[556,614,1761,1782]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, Male, 2A, head and pronotum; 2B–2D, penial armature (2B dorsal, 2C ventral and 2D lateral views). Scales: Fig. 2A 1.0 mm; Figs. 2B–2D 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1858,2027]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,573]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="145" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">
Nymph: General color brownish. Head brown with lighter areas near post-frontal suture and in frontoclypeal region (
<figureCitation box="[241,333,1894,1919]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[347,1253,643,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[325,1270,631,1923]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3 A – 3 F. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Nymph, 3 A, head; 3 B, right mandible; 3 C, right maxilla; 3 D, labium; 3 E, prothoracic left leg; 3 F, cerci proximal, medial and distal. Scales: Figs. 3 A, 3 E, 3 F: 1.0 mm; Figs. 3 B, 3 C, 3 D: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801873/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); M-line complete, distinct; eyes black and ocelli black with a darker stain medially. Pronotum brownish with median line and sparse areas yellowish (
<figureCitation box="[780,871,1930,1955]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[347,1253,643,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[325,1270,631,1923]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3 A – 3 F. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Nymph, 3 A, head; 3 B, right mandible; 3 C, right maxilla; 3 D, labium; 3 E, prothoracic left leg; 3 F, cerci proximal, medial and distal. Scales: Figs. 3 A, 3 E, 3 F: 1.0 mm; Figs. 3 B, 3 C, 3 D: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801873/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Mandibles, maxillae, and labium as in 
<figureCitation box="[1333,1410,1930,1955]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[347,1253,643,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[325,1270,631,1923]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3 A – 3 F. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Nymph, 3 A, head; 3 B, right mandible; 3 C, right maxilla; 3 D, labium; 3 E, prothoracic left leg; 3 F, cerci proximal, medial and distal. Scales: Figs. 3 A, 3 E, 3 F: 1.0 mm; Figs. 3 B, 3 C, 3 D: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801873/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
B, 3C, 3D. Forefemur with lateral surface covered by scattered bristles (
<figureCitation box="[940,1008,1966,1991]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[347,1253,643,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[325,1270,631,1923]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3 A – 3 F. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Nymph, 3 A, head; 3 B, right mandible; 3 C, right maxilla; 3 D, labium; 3 E, prothoracic left leg; 3 F, cerci proximal, medial and distal. Scales: Figs. 3 A, 3 E, 3 F: 1.0 mm; Figs. 3 B, 3 C, 3 D: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801873/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
E); dorsally and ventrally with higher density of thick bristles; dorsally with translucent fringe of hairs. Tibia ventrally with thin and sparse translucent bristles, and dorsally with a row of thick bristles in the border and a well-developed band of hairs. Cerci brown with thick bristles; segments differ in shape and size from base to apex (
<figureCitation box="[993,1062,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[347,1253,643,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[325,1270,631,1923]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3 A – 3 F. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Nymph, 3 A, head; 3 B, right mandible; 3 C, right maxilla; 3 D, labium; 3 E, prothoracic left leg; 3 F, cerci proximal, medial and distal. Scales: Figs. 3 A, 3 E, 3 F: 1.0 mm; Figs. 3 B, 3 C, 3 D: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801873/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
E). Thoracic gills: 
<collectionCode box="[1280,1342,188,212]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15857" name="Northern Arizona University" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">ASC</collectionCode>
1, PSC1, AT2, AT3 and PT3 (sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Shepard" box="[449,729,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" refString="Shepard, W. D. &amp; Stewart, K. W. (1983) Comparative study of nymphal gills in North American stonefly genera and a new, proposed paradigm of Plecoptera gill evolution. Miscellaneous Publication Entomological Society of America, 13, 1 - 57." type="journal article" year="1983">Shepard &amp; Stewart 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Stewart" box="[741,989,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" refString="Stewart, K. W. &amp; Stark, K. W. (2002) Nymphs of North American Stonefly Genera (Plecoptera). Caddis Press, Columbus, Ohio, 510 pp." type="book" year="2002">Stewart &amp; Stark 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Measurements (n=7): head width 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0999999999999996" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" unit="mm" value="3.0999999999999996" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="2.9">2.9– 3.3 mm</quantity>
; head length 
<quantity box="[389,527,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="1.9">1.9–2.6 mm</quantity>
; antennae length 4.0–5.0mm; pronotum width 
<quantity box="[1051,1168,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–3 mm</quantity>
; pronotum length 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
; cercal length 
<quantity box="[360,498,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" unit="mm" value="7.0" valueMax="7.5" valueMin="6.5">6.5–7.5 mm</quantity>
; total length 
<quantity box="[643,760,296,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.45" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="7.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" unit="mm" value="8.45" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.9">7.9–9 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
