<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="145" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">Remarks.</emphasis>
The color of the adult is similar to many species of the genus. The penial armature of 
<taxonomicName box="[1326,1404,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pitii">
<emphasis box="[1326,1404,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">A. pitii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[309,377,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1760,1783]" captionTargetBox="[339,1248,415,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[323,1268,405,1738]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – 2 D. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Male, 2 A, head and pronotum; 2 B – 2 D, penial armature (2 B dorsal, 2 C ventral and 2 D lateral views). Scales: Fig. 2 A 1.0 mm; Figs. 2 B – 2 D 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801871/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
C) and lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[613,681,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1760,1783]" captionTargetBox="[339,1248,415,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[323,1268,405,1738]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – 2 D. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Male, 2 A, head and pronotum; 2 B – 2 D, penial armature (2 B dorsal, 2 C ventral and 2 D lateral views). Scales: Fig. 2 A 1.0 mm; Figs. 2 B – 2 D 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801871/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D) is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Baldin" authorityName="Baldin" authorityYear="2013" box="[927,1297,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itatiaiensis">
<emphasis box="[927,1083,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">A. itatiaiensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Baldin" box="[1091,1297,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" refString="Baldin, C., Bispo, P. C. &amp; Novaes, M. C. (2013) New species and records of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Rio de Janeiro State, Brazil. Zootaxa, 3694 (4), 391 - 397." type="journal article" year="2013">
Baldin 
<emphasis box="[1175,1233,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">et. al</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
also known from southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[367,438,404,429]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, but differs in the size of membranous vesicles and apex. In 
<emphasis box="[1159,1246,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">
<taxonomicName box="[1159,1242,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pitii">A. pitii</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the vesicles are smaller and are more medially than in 
<taxonomicName box="[586,741,440,463]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itatiaiensis">
<emphasis box="[586,741,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">A. itatiaiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The penial armature (
<figureCitation box="[998,1075,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1760,1783]" captionTargetBox="[339,1248,415,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[323,1268,405,1738]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – 2 D. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Male, 2 A, head and pronotum; 2 B – 2 D, penial armature (2 B dorsal, 2 C ventral and 2 D lateral views). Scales: Fig. 2 A 1.0 mm; Figs. 2 B – 2 D 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801871/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
B–2D) of 
<taxonomicName box="[1190,1267,440,463]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pitii">
<emphasis box="[1190,1267,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">A. pitii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more robust basally than 
<emphasis box="[291,452,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">
<taxonomicName box="[291,448,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itatiaiensis">A. itatiaiensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[634,701,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1760,1783]" captionTargetBox="[339,1248,415,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[323,1268,405,1738]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 A – 2 D. Anacroneuria pitii sp. n., Male, 2 A, head and pronotum; 2 B – 2 D, penial armature (2 B dorsal, 2 C ventral and 2 D lateral views). Scales: Fig. 2 A 1.0 mm; Figs. 2 B – 2 D 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/801871/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D), the apex of 
<taxonomicName box="[872,947,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pitii">
<emphasis box="[872,947,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">A. pitii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is thinner than 
<taxonomicName box="[1120,1273,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itatiaiensis">
<emphasis box="[1120,1273,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">A. itatiaiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the hooks are more robust in 
<taxonomicName box="[321,389,512,535]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piti">
<emphasis box="[321,389,512,535]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">A. piti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore the color of 
<taxonomicName box="[686,763,512,535]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pitii">
<emphasis box="[686,763,512,535]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">A. pitii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is lighter than 
<taxonomicName box="[931,1085,512,535]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itatiaiensis">
<emphasis box="[931,1085,512,535]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">A. itatiaiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1304,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,573]" box="[199,1304,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">Etymology.</emphasis>
The patronym honors Pitágoras da Conceição Bispo, a Brazilian 
<taxonomicName box="[1066,1184,548,573]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Plecoptera</taxonomicName>
specialist.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
